Key Match Events: Ragans struck out 10 and tied a club record with eight consecutive strikeouts between the first and third innings.
Post-Match Reflections: Ragans said, 'Good for five [innings] and terrible for one.'
Ragans added, 'I don't play for records, I play to win,' and 'Records are cool, but all I want to do is win, in whichever way that comes.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Royals (75-62) remain 2 1/2 games behind the Guardians (77-59) for first place in the American League Central.
They still hold the second AL Wild Card spot and are a game ahead of the Twins for the third and final position.
